[08:35:30.196][VCOM] For SUN_FSK  : whitening
[08:35:30.202][VCOM] For SUN_OFDM : scrambler
[08:35:30.207][VCOM] For SUN_OQPSK: rateMode
[08:35:30.221][VCOM] trigModeSwitchTx    Transmit a Mode Switch packet then transmit packets on the new PHY with current
[08:35:30.224][VCOM] TX options Depending on modeSwitchLife configuration, after all iterations are
[08:35:30.232][VCOM] done, it either stays on the new PHY or returns to the base PHY.
[08:35:30.239][VCOM] [uint8] new PhyModeId, i.e. ID of the PHYMode we are switching to
[08:35:30.244][VCOM] [uint8] number of packets transmitted on the new PHY
[08:35:30.254][VCOM] [uint32opt] number of times the sequence -mode switch packet followed by data packets- is
[08:35:30.259][VCOM] repeated, default is 1 if argument is absent
[08:35:30.269][VCOM] [uint32opt] delayMilliseconds before switching back to base PHY after all packets have been
[08:35:30.280][VCOM] transmitted on the new PHY, default is 0 if argument is absent. Multitimer is
[08:35:30.283][VCOM] used for delay greater than 0.
[08:35:30.291][VCOM] modeSwitchLife      Return to the base PHY after all data packets transmission for TX or after
[08:35:30.300][VCOM] MODE_SWITCH_START event and multitimer expiration after first data packet
[08:35:30.305][VCOM] reception on new phy for RX.
[08:35:30.315][VCOM] [uint8] 0=stay on new PHY (normal Wi-SUN FAN behaviour) 1=return to base PHY (special test mode)
